WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.535 --> 00:00:04.471
"Order the following pizza
for the Taskmaster

00:00:04.471 --> 00:00:06.807
without using any of
the following words."

00:00:06.807 --> 00:00:09.009
"Extra large pizza
with pepperoni,

00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:10.544
peppers, pepper..."

00:00:10.544 --> 00:00:14.314
"Pineapple, tuna, and dill."

00:00:14.314 --> 00:00:18.085
"Most accurate pizza order
and vocabulary wins."

00:00:18.085 --> 00:00:19.353
"Also, you get an extra point

00:00:19.353 --> 00:00:22.456
if you can make the pizza person
say the word 'bubbles.'"

00:00:22.456 --> 00:00:24.458
[ Laughter ]

00:00:24.458 --> 00:00:25.626
Oh, my God.

00:00:25.626 --> 00:00:26.793
Man: Yeah.
Thanks for calling Johnny's.

00:00:26.793 --> 00:00:27.928
May I help you?

00:00:27.928 --> 00:00:29.529
Hold on.

00:00:29.529 --> 00:00:30.998
It's Lisa.
How are you?

00:00:30.998 --> 00:00:32.866
[ Laughter and applause ]

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:35.135
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:38.338
We're going to see Lisa,
Freddie, and Ron, first of all.

00:00:38.338 --> 00:00:40.274
-Okay. We're a team.
-Yes.

00:00:40.274 --> 00:00:42.309
Woman: Hello?
Hi. How are you?

00:00:42.309 --> 00:00:44.211
Good. How are you?
Doing wonderful.

00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:46.046
I was wondering
if I could place an order.

00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:47.180
Okay.
What would you like?

00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:48.215
Man:
Lou's Pizza.

00:00:48.215 --> 00:00:49.316
Afternoon.
How are you doing?

00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:50.884
Good.
How are you doing?

00:00:50.884 --> 00:00:52.719
Wonderfully.
Yeah, nice -- nice day.

00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:55.522
Beautiful, uh, weather.
[ Laughter ]

00:00:55.522 --> 00:00:57.124
You know,
it's the perfect time for,

00:00:57.124 --> 00:00:59.126
you know, ordering
what you need.

00:00:59.126 --> 00:01:00.360
Yeah, man.
Listen to me.

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:01.962
You know the round
things you sell?

00:01:01.962 --> 00:01:04.464
They're made out of dough
and sauce and cheese?

00:01:04.464 --> 00:01:06.800
Man: We have a calzone,
but it doesn't come with sauce.

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:08.969
The flat thing.

00:01:08.969 --> 00:01:10.470
What's the biggest size
you have?

00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:12.639
-Extra large.
-Okay, I'll do that.

00:01:12.639 --> 00:01:14.574
Then what's the
biggest you have?

00:01:14.574 --> 00:01:16.343
-Large.
-No, it's not.

00:01:16.343 --> 00:01:19.846
Can you make mine
a little bit more big?

00:01:19.846 --> 00:01:21.648
I'd like a very big one,
please.

00:01:21.648 --> 00:01:23.684
-What size?
-The biggest.

00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:24.918
[ Line hangs up ]

00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:27.154
Hello? Hello?

00:01:27.154 --> 00:01:28.522
[ Laughter ]

00:01:28.522 --> 00:01:30.090
He just hung up on me.

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:33.694
Like, I want the --
I want --

00:01:33.694 --> 00:01:35.929
I'm sorry.
I don't order that many pizzas.

00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:37.531
[ Buzzer ]
[ Light laughter, groaning ]

00:01:37.531 --> 00:01:39.433
What kind of pizza toppings
do you have?

00:01:39.433 --> 00:01:40.701
[ Buzzer ]
[ Audience groans ]

00:01:40.701 --> 00:01:41.868
[ Line rings ]

00:01:41.868 --> 00:01:43.270
-Hello?
-Hi. Hi there.

00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:44.638
I think we got cut off.

00:01:44.638 --> 00:01:46.039
Can I order the pizza?
Is that all right?

00:01:46.039 --> 00:01:47.274
[ Buzzer ]

00:01:47.274 --> 00:01:49.943
-Extra tomato, green pepper.
-I think that one.

00:01:49.943 --> 00:01:51.712
-Pepperoni, sausage --
-That one!

00:01:51.712 --> 00:01:53.613
Wait!
What's the first one?

00:01:53.613 --> 00:01:55.048
-So you what toppings?
-Okay. Shh!

00:01:55.048 --> 00:01:56.550
-Do you want --
-You run through them.

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:58.618
I'll just say, "Yes, yes, yes."
Okay. Go.

00:01:58.618 --> 00:01:59.820
[ Line hangs up ]

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:02.689
Hello? He hung up.
[ Laughter and applause ]

00:02:02.689 --> 00:02:05.792
Could I have a Hawaiian one
without the ham?

00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:07.694
What would you put in
instead of ham?

00:02:07.694 --> 00:02:10.030
-What do you want?
-A very -- Something very...

00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:11.331
Sorry. I've just
forgotten the...

00:02:11.331 --> 00:02:13.133
[ Line rings ]

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:15.402
They're not even answering now.
They, like, blew me off.

00:02:15.402 --> 00:02:17.904
-Johnny's. How may I help?
-Just one last question.

00:02:17.904 --> 00:02:20.107
[ Chuckling ] Do you have
any fruit that you put on top?

00:02:20.107 --> 00:02:21.475
Type of fruit? No.
[ Line hangs up ]

00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:23.477
[ Laughter ]

00:02:23.477 --> 00:02:28.248
Just sprinkle on a little bit
of, um, salt and thingy, the...

00:02:28.248 --> 00:02:29.383
Man: What?

00:02:29.383 --> 00:02:32.119
Salt and --
and its [Chuckling] friend.

00:02:32.119 --> 00:02:33.186
[ Laughter ]

00:02:33.186 --> 00:02:34.654
Okay.

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:42.496
Please give me one food item.

00:02:42.496 --> 00:02:43.997
Do you want me to take that
to the shop?

00:02:43.997 --> 00:02:45.699
[ Laughs ]

00:02:45.699 --> 00:02:46.800
Go.

00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:48.502
-Thanks, Lisa.
-Bye.
84
